</ul>
<h3>"Initiation à la linogravure" (Introduction to linocut printmaking - presented in French)</h3>
<p>October 5 from 1 pm to 5 pm<br>
Ages 16 and up<br>
Cost: $77.21 + tax (per person)<br>
<a href="https://anc.ca.apm.activecommunities.com/ottawa/activity/search/detail/137496?onlineSiteId=0&amp;locale=fr-CA&amp;from_original_cui=true">Advance registration is required.&nbsp;</a></p>
<p>Discover the basics of linocut printmaking and create your own greeting cards. Participants will familiarize themselves with the tools of the trade and learn beginner-friendly techniques to transfer an image onto an engraving block, carve the design, ink a block, and print the final product. You’ll leave with six cards to share with friends and family. All skill levels, including beginners, are welcome. A selection of design templates will be provided to spark inspiration. Supplies are included in the cost of registration. Light refreshments will be served.</p>
<p><strong>Notes:</strong></p>
<ul>
